reviews.headline: Not very effective
reviews.comments: I've been using this eye cream for at least 3 months now, & I haven't noticed any improvements. I have dark circles under my eyes that I thought would lighten some, but sadly they have not. I wouldn't necessarily say the skin feels any firmer/tighter either. I don't have any eye wrinkles so I can't speak on whether it helps with that. For the price, I expected much better results.

reviews.headline: Best eye cream that I have used
reviews.comments: This is the best eye cream that I have used. I have super sensitive skin and usually everytime I try an eye cream it either doesn't work like it is supposed to or makes my eyes water all day. With IT Confidence in an eye cream, my eyes don't water, the dark circles are visibly lighter and around my eyes are moisturized and the lines are lighter. I will absolutely buy again.

reviews.headline: I keep buying
reviews.comments: I have been using this for over 6 months now.i love how it goes on, you do not need to much.  It just absorbs into your skin.  I can see that the lines under and around my eyes are starting so go away.  This is part of my daily routine along with other IT beauty products.  Just turning 50 taking my skin regimen seriously, and this is part of it.

reviews.headline: Not moisturizing
reviews.comments: This cream dries out the skin around my eyes during the day causing a dry layer around the eyes which is not pretty.  I do not feel any benefit in using this cream. I would not go back to buy again.

reviews.headline: Not for sensitive skin
reviews.comments: I really wanted to like this sm I think IT is a good brand but this irritated my eyes the first night I tried this. I put it on for one or two more nights to make sure it was this and not something else, and it was definitely this. I do have some skin sensitivities but nothing major. So if you have sensitive skin I'd avoid

reviews.headline: Have repurchased several times now
reviews.comments: I entered my 40s and noticed that I was starting to get hooded eyelids. I read a lot of reviews and chose this cream. It *does* burn a little when you start using it, which tells you something is happening. I use it in the AM to perk up my eyes

reviews.headline: Don't get this
reviews.comments: It did absolutely nothing for me and when I used it at night and applied make up the next day it would be very patchy under my eyes.

reviews.headline: Don't get this
reviews.comments: It did absolutely nothing for me and when I used it at night and applied make up the next day it would be very patchy under my eyes.

reviews.headline: Not good
reviews.comments: Burns my eyes and made them so dry!

reviews.headline: not for sensitive skin
reviews.comments: tried this product and the instant it went on it burned and irritated my skin. I had to wash it off immediately. do not recommend for sensitive skin.

reviews.headline: Did they change the formula?
reviews.comments: Used to love this profict. But started using it and within hours my skin was red, inflammed and hot to the touch. Thought it might of been my sunscreen or facewash. But nopeâ€¦ it was this. Shame. It was perfect. Wish they wouldn't of messed with the formula becuae its a nope for me if you have sensitive skin.

reviews.headline: 3rd Buy
reviews.comments: This cream is really great. It has lightened my under eye area dramatically, so those with darkness would definitely benefit. I actually didn't get this thinking it would lighten my eye area, but was pleasantly surprised. It's very hydrating and helps fine lines.

reviews.headline: Sampler- would consider buying
reviews.comments: I'm new to buying eye creams and they can get pretty pricey. I had just a sampler version, I really enjoyed it. I have oily skin but it moisturized nicely and had creamy texture.

reviews.headline: Burning, crusts up, feels waxy
reviews.comments: I was excited to try this. I was trying to find a replacement for Glamglow BrightEyes eye cream. It burns the skin under my eyes and as the day goes on it gets into the eye and irritates it too. I bought this as part of a set.

reviews.headline: Moisturized eyes
reviews.comments: I have dark circles because of genetics and this product does help a little, i dont ever expect any product to take my dark circles away completely but my eyes do feel moisturized and my skin is not so loose and wrinkley. I have sensitive skin and this product does not cause me irritation.

reviews.headline: Avoid!
reviews.comments:
I received a sample size over a year ago, added it to my skin care routine at night. Woke up with itchy, irritated eyes after the first night so I threw it away. However, last month I purchased an IT Confidence gift set that contained the moisturizer (which I love), Cleanser, and eye cream. I decided to try the eye cream again, thinking it had been over a year so maybe the formula was improved.....wrong! I decided to try the eye cream and within hours my eyes are irritated, swollen, and itchy. I avoided getting too close to my eye lids, focusing on lower underlying, but it still managed to irritate my eyes!
Don't even take a chance to see if you're one of the few who wouldn't react to this. Find another eye cream and save the money. I'm just glad I basically got it free in a gift set, or else I'd return it.

reviews.headline: Burning
reviews.comments: Please heed the warnings of the others. I did not because I dont have sensitive skin and have never had an issue with an eye cream. I only used the cream twice. The first time I didn't notice an issue but woke up the next morning with crusty eyes. I didnt think much of it and put a small amount on that morning. Almost instantly my skin under my eyes started burning. I developed swelling and red blotchy patches under my eyes where I applied the cream. Will definitely be returning.

reviews.headline: Does not layer well.
reviews.comments: I, like many, thought this would be an amazing peptide cream! And while it does work pretty well alone, I DO NOT recommend wearing this under makeup or with makeup. Don't out concealer over it or mix it with any makeup. Forget the makeup tips, they do not work. Just west it alone on a no makeup day or a day you are not wearing any makeup. Other than that, its a decent product.

reviews.headline: It's OK
reviews.comments: the product works.  I do see a noticeable difference within a half hour of putting this under my eyes.  However, something about this makes my eyes slightly itchy.  No redness or anything for me thankfully.

reviews.headline: i would NOT buy this product again.
reviews.comments:
Unfortunately, after several days of using this product, I broke out in a rash on my face.  I immediately returned the product and was given a full refund.  I have sensitive skin and sometimes have issues with various skin products....unfortunately, the issue sometimes doesn't show up for a few days.

If you don't have sensitive skin, this product may work for you.  If you do have sensitive skin, I'd try something else.
